messages.message: ah looking into slow loading, could you move/copy this project into a shared workspace? right now I have no access and my aihub-sandbox projects aren't reproducing this

woah that worked! even though im signed in with my other account huh

So I think I know what's happening:
• I fixed the table rendering issue by marking all fields extracted with flash-extraction with a flag (and that gets stored with the extracted values), and we check that flag for rendering
• The values for the record were extracted before my changes, so they don't have the flag (I checked this in the extracted_fields endpoint response earlier), so they don't get processed to render correctly
I'm trying to re-run flash extraction to verify completely, but like all the other jobs, it's just stuck perpetually on sandbox internal :sweat_smile: Pauline is already trying to unblock our job queue so I'll wait for her progress there

alrightyy, synced with charles to run his proj fields and the line items field auto-re-ran while we were looking at it and it loads properly :raised_hands: so this issue should be resolved for old fields that are re-ran and all new fields :white_check_mark:
